00:35:06.490 --> 00:35:11.330
in fact, the sum of two separate
curves. And, there's a mathematical

00:35:11.330 --> 00:35:16.160
technique called deconvolution that
says if the blue curve were the sum

00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:35.320
of two properly configured curves,
what would they look like?

00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:24.860
And so, what you do is you
deconvolve the blue curve into the

00:35:24.860 --> 00:35:28.730
red and green curve.
So, if there were a red curve of

00:35:28.730 --> 00:35:32.590
this magnitude,
and a green curve of this magnitude,

00:35:32.590 --> 00:35:36.460
with the right symmetry, they would
sum to give us the blue curve.

00:35:36.460 --> 00:35:40.330
And furthermore, we see that
