00:45:42.920 --> 00:45:46.460
and then I'm going to take this part
and expand it,

00:45:46.460 --> 00:46:06.320
OK? And, I'm going to divide the
top into two zones.

00:45:30.000 --> 00:45:54.280
So, this is fast cooling.
And, the center is slow cooling.

00:45:54.280 --> 00:45:58.570
And, likewise on the bottom side.
So, what happens? If you look on

00:45:58.570 --> 00:46:02.850
this trace, it says fast cooling
gives me high excess volume.

00:46:02.850 --> 00:46:07.140
So, I could say that when this is
finished, I could characterize it as

00:46:07.140 --> 00:46:11.420
follows: that because the upper
portion cooled quickly,

00:46:11.420 --> 00:46:15.710
it should occupy a large volume.
And, the lower portion cooled

00:46:15.710 --> 00:46:34.286
slowly. It wants to occupy
a smaller volume.

00:46:00.000 --> 00:46:24.260
But, they are joined.
